<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Before start</h2><a id="user-content-before-start" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Before start" href="#before-start"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>


<ul dir="auto">


<li>MacOS have CPU Core limit (64 cores) in my case with x2 Intel Xeon E5 2699 v3, i disable 2 core on both CPU in bios, without it system can't boot</li>


<li>Don't forget generate and set in config.plist you own MLB/Serial etc</li>


<li>You should use exactly same bios settings like in repo BIOS folder, most of problem with booting installer and system in bios settings</li>


<li>For working WiFi/BT/Airdrop etc...you should use OpenCore Legacy Patcher Developers builds from <a href="https://github.com/dortania/OpenCore-Legacy-Patcher">https://github.com/dortania/OpenCore-Legacy-Patcher</a></li>


<li>I use self made bios mod with -50mv undervolting and turbo boost unlock, but it's not necessary to start the system</li>


</ul>


<p dir="auto"><strong>macOS version</strong>: 15 beta 4</p>


<p dir="auto"><strong>OpenCore version</strong>: 1.1</p>


<p dir="auto"><strong>SMBIOS</strong>: iMacPro1,1</p>
